  <Subject Subject_ID="300055192">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300055148</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>psychological concepts [300055148], social science concepts [300239103], Associated Concepts (hierarchy name) [300055126], Associated Concepts Facet [300264086]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the fact or condition of knowing something with familiarity gained through experience or association, as in the acquaintance with or understanding of a science, art, or technique. Also refers to the body of knowledge, or range of information acquired by study, investigation, observation, or experience.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046693/Merriam-Webster's Collegiate Dictionary [online] (1997-2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al hecho o condición de saber algo con familiaridad adquirido a través de la experiencia o asociación, como en la relación con la comprensión de una ciencia, arte o técnica. También se refiere al cuerpo de conocimiento o rango de información adquirido por el estudio, investigación, observación o experiencia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Het weet hebben van iets op basis van ervaring of associatie, zoals men op de hoogte kan zijn van de wetenschap, kunst of techniek. Verwijst ook naar het geheel aan informatie dat kan worden verworven door studie, onderzoek, observaties of ervaring.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>意指透過經驗或聯想，而能夠熟悉進而了解某件事情；這種事實或狀態就稱為知識，其包括認識或了解某種科學、藝術或技巧。此外，亦指透過研究、調查、觀察或經驗而獲得的一整套知識或一系列資訊。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
